id: pmc-s1c1
title: Stabilize full-history release windows for release automation
description: "Follow-up from pm-cli#62 bot review: full-history changelog generation should preserve empty tag windows, ignore matching tags not merged into HEAD, and support preparing a pending release window with --release-version so release pipeline output matches post-tag CI checks."
type: Issue
status: closed
priority: 1
tags[3]: changelog,release,review
created_at: "2026-05-24T16:21:29.997Z"
updated_at: "2026-05-25T20:04:49.742Z"
author: codex-pm-changelog-review
release: v2026.05.24-15
resolution: "Full-history mode now preserves empty release windows, limits git release tags to tags merged into HEAD, and supports a pending release window from --release-version/--date so release prep and post-tag CI use the same generated changelog shape."
expected_result: "pm-changelog full-history mode can be used consistently by release prep and CI, preserving complete tag history and avoiding unrelated branch tags."
actual_result: "pm-changelog@2026.5.24-15 includes the review fixes with regression tests for empty windows, unmerged tags, annotated tag commit dates, and pending release windows."
